{
  "texts": [
    "This creates a document-term matrix where each row represents a document (CV or job posting), and each column represents a unique word.",
    "The document term matrix produced from this step was then used as the input to the similarity calculation step.",
    "Cosine similarity calculationCosine similarity between each CV and job posting pair was calculated using the document-term matrix obtained from countvectorizer.",
    "Cosine similarity measures the similarity between two vectors by calculating the cosine of the angle between them.",
    "It ranges from 0 (no similarity) to 1 (perfect similarity)."
  ]
